===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|あに|yomi=k}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=あに|-}} of unclear derivation:
* Probably originally a compound of {{compound|ja|吾|tr1=a|pos1=Eastern Old Japanese first-person pronoun|の|tr2=no|pos2=possessive particle|兄|tr3=ye → e|t3=[[eldest]] [[sibling]]|pos3=see below}}:<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>
*: {{IPAfont|⟨a no<sub>2</sub> ye⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/anʉʲɨe/}} → {{IPAchar|/ani/}}
* Alternatively, an [[apophony|apophonic]] form of {{m|ja|姉|tr=ane||[[elder]] [[sister]]}}, itself possibly from the same derivation above.<ref>{{cite-book|ja|year=1929|author=Matsuoka Shizuo|title=ja:日本古語大辞典|url=https://dl.ndl.go.jp/info:ndljp/pid/1145583 |page=56|passage=之からアニといふ語が分派した|translation=The word ''ani'' developed from this|section=アネ（姉）|trans-title=Comprehensive Dictionary of Archaic Japanese}}</ref>
* Several other theories have also been suggested.<ref name="KDJ"/>

